parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden lock-up of the steering wheel can cause loss of control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded, especially at high speeds or during turns.
symptoms: The steering wheel locks up
becomes difficult to turn
or freezes
making it hard to control the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering pump can cause loss of power assist, making it difficult to steer, especially at low speeds, which can lead to accidents or increase the risk of driver fatigue.
symptoms: The power steering pump fails
causing a loss of power assist
making the steering wheel harder to turn.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering hose can cause fluid leaks, leading to a loss of power assist, making it difficult to steer, especially at low speeds, which can lead to accidents or increase the risk of driver fatigue.
symptoms: The power steering hose fails
causing fluid leaks
leading to a loss of power assist
making the steering wheel harder to turn.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering wheel spring kit can cause the steering wheel to malfunction, leading to loss of control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The steering wheel spring kit fails
causing the steering wheel to malfunction
making it hard to control the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake rotors can cause uneven braking, noise, and vibration, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Noise when braking
brake rotors excessively worn
brake rotors warped or damaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake lockup and ABS malfunction can cause the vehicle to skid or lose control, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Brakes lock up
vehicle skids when braking
ABS braking system engages unnecessarily
traction control system turns on when making turns.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded. In extreme cases, a faulty fuel pump can also cause a spark, potentially leading to a fire.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or fails to start
the fuel pump makes a loud whining or grinding noise
the fuel pump overheats
the vehicle experiences poor engine performance
the fuel pump electrical connector or wiring shows signs of damage or burning.
